  "prompt": "What is the chemical formula for ammonium acetate?",
  "response": "The chemical formula for **ammonium acetate** is **NH\u2084CH\u2083COO** or alternatively **CH\u2083COONH\u2084**.\n\n**Breakdown of the Formula:**\n- **Ammonium (NH\u2084\u207a):** This is the positively charged ion.\n- **Acetate (CH\u2083COO\u207b):** This is the negatively charged ion derived from acetic acid.\n\nWhen combined, they form the neutral compound ammonium acetate:\n\n**NH\u2084\u207a + CH\u2083COO\u207b \u2192 NH\u2084CH\u2083COO**\n\n**Alternative Representation:**\nSometimes, the formula is written as **CH\u2083COONH\u2084**, which conveys the same stoichiometry but places the acetate group first.\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Chemical Formula:** NH\u2084CH\u2083COO or CH\u2083COONH\u2084",
